{"id":"1881","name":"bright-early-playing-it-cool-edition","title":"Bright &amp; Early: Playing It Cool Edition","author":"Christy Frink","date":"2009-05-28T09:45:00-05:00","tags":["bankruptcy","censorship","donelson christian academy","ft. campbell","gm","jackie and me","karl dean","madeline embrey","racism","regional mass transit","restructuring","scripps national spelling bee","spelling bee","spring hill","st. bernard academy","suicides","tennessee ethics commission"],"categories":["News"],"contentEncoded":"<div id=\"greet_block\"><noscript><div class=\"greet_block wpgb_cornered\"><div class=\"greet_text\"><div class=\"greet_image\"><a href=\"http://nashvillest.com/feed/rss/\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"http://nashvillest.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-greet-box/images/rss_icon.png\" alt=\"WP Greet Box icon\"></a></div>Hello there! If you&apos;re new to Nashvillest, you might want to <a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/nashvillest\" rel=\"nofollow\"><strong>subscribe to our RSS feed</strong></a> to make sure you don&apos;t miss anything! We&apos;re also on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/#!/nashvillest\" target=\"blank\"><strong>Twitter</strong></a> if you&apos;d like to join us there!<div style=\"clear:both\"></div><div class=\"greet_block_powered_by\">Powered by <a href=\"http://omninoggin.com/projects/wordpress-plugins/wp-greet-box-wordpress-plugin/\" title=\"WP Greet Box WordPress Plugin\" style=\"text-decoration:none;\">WP Greet Box</a> <a href=\"http://omninoggin.com/\" title=\"WordPress Plugin\" style=\"text-decoration:none;\">WordPress Plugin</a></div><div style=\"clear:both\"></div></div></div></noscript></div><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/fallingwater123/3559854222/in/pool-nashvillest\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.flickr.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3396/3559854222_8a8cd59d0c.jpg?v=1243190608\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"379\"></a></p><p>Good morning, Nashville. The June 1 deadline for bankruptcy filing is closing in quickly for GM, <a href=\"http://www.wkrn.com/global/story.asp?s=10433323\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.wkrn.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">whose stocks have fallen a painful 15% since yesterday morning</a>. In the meantime, GM officials are working on a restructuring plan that <a href=\"http://www.wkrn.com/global/story.asp?s=10419426\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.wkrn.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">could completely shut down the manufacturing plant in Spring Hill, eliminating thousands of jobs</a>. Though Congressman Jim Cooper seems pretty confident that Spring Hill won&#x2019;t be affected, everyone else is preparing for the worst.</p><ul><li><strong>Cosmotell-what?</strong> Congrats to <a href=\"http://www.tennessean.com/article/20090528/NEWS04/905280329/-1/RSS05\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.tennessean.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_self\">St. Bernard Academy 7th grader  Madeline Embrey who made it much farther in the Scripps National Spelling Bee than we ever could</a>. Unfortunately she missed out on the final round after coming up slightly short on a written test, but she can still spell &#x201C;cosmotelluria&#x201D; and we don&#x2019;t even know what that means.</li><li><strong>Diff&#x2019;rent strokes for diff&#x2019;rent folks. </strong>A Donelson Christian Academy student&#x2019;s parents are <a href=\"http://www.newschannel5.com/global/story.asp?s=10435096\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.newschannel5.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">probably withdrawing their kid from the school after they found the book <em>Jackie and Me</em> on the student&#x2019;s assigned reading list</a>. The book talks about baseball legend Jackie Robinson and his experience with racism in the 1940s while using some colorful but probably historically accurate language.</li><li><strong>Bits &amp; pieces. </strong>The <a href=\"http://www.tennessean.com/article/20090528/NEWS0201/905280340/-1/RSS05\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.tennessean.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">Tennessee Ethics Commission is probably going to expire</a> in June, for real, because who needs ethics anyway? &#x2026; Mayor Dean continues to talk about how we <a href=\"http://www.tennessean.com/article/20090528/NEWS01/905280341/-1/RSS05\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.tennessean.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">really, really need better regional mass transit</a> &#x2026; Fort Campbell still <a href=\"http://politics.nashvillepost.com/2009/05/27/fort-campbell-leads-army-in-suicides/\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;politics.nashvillepost.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">leads the Army in suicides</a>, averaging about one suicide per week.</li></ul><p><em>Photo by <a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/fallingwater123/3559854222/in/pool-nashvillest\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.flickr.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">fallingwater123</a>.</em></p><p>Related posts:<ol><li><a href=\"http://nashvillest.com/2008/07/09/bright-early-playing-with-fire-edition/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent Link: Bright &amp; Early: Playing With Fire Edition\">Bright &amp; Early: Playing With Fire Edition</a></li></ol></p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<!--END .entry-content .article-->"}